Migros was unchanged at 26.3 liras.  Tofas Turk Otomobil Fabrikasi AS (TOASO)  : The Turkish
unit of Fiat SpA in partnership with  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL)  
started a third shift at its plant in the western city of Bursa
to meet new orders, Aksam reported. Tofas is employing 400 new
workers to meet the demand, which will increase in the final
quarter as it starts to produce the Opel Combo van model, the
newspaper said, citing chief executive Ali Pandir. Tofas fell 8
kurus, or 0.9 percent, to 8.66 liras. Koc slipped 2 kurus, or
